"title": "5076: Abraham, life of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5076",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God called Abraham to live as a nomad in Canaan and promised the land to his descendants, naming him “father of many”, although he had no heir until his old age.</p>\n<h2>Abraham's ancestors, marriage and descendants</h2>\n<h3>The line of descent from Shem to Abraham</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr1:24-1Chr1:27\">1CH 1:24–1:27</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham's marriage to Sarah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:29-Gen11:30\">GEN 11:29–11:30</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham's descendants</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr1:28-1Chr1:34\">1CH 1:28–1:34</a></p>\n<h2>Abraham was called to live in Canaan</h2>\n<h3>His migration from Ur to Canaan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:31-Gen12:5\">GEN 11:31–12:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:2-Josh24:3\">JOS 24:2–24:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:2-Acts7:4\">ACT 7:2–7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8-Heb11:9\">HEB 11:8–11:9</a></p>\n<h3>His nomadic way of life in Canaan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:9\">HEB 11:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:6-Gen12:10\">GEN 12:6–12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:1-Gen13:4\">GEN 13:1–13:4</a></p>\n<h3>God gives Abraham his new name</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:5\">GEN 17:5</a></strong> <em>The giving of a new name signifies a new relationship to God. “Abram” has the sense of “revered father”, whereas “Abraham” means “father of many people”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:15\">GEN 17:15</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham buys a burial site for Sarah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:3-Gen23:4\">GEN 23:3–23:4</a></strong> <em>This is his only acquisition of land in Canaan.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:17-Gen23:20\">GEN 23:17–23:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:29-Gen49:32\">GEN 49:29–49:32</a></p>\n<h2>Abraham's dealings with his nephew, Lot</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:4-Gen12:5\">GEN 12:4–12:5</a> <em>Abraham is accompanied to Canaan by Lot</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:5-Gen13:12\">GEN 13:5–13:12</a> <em>Abraham and Lot separate</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:8-Gen14:16\">GEN 14:8–14:16</a> <em>Abraham rescues Lot from five local kings.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:20-Gen18:33\">GEN 18:20–18:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:29\">GEN 19:29</a></p>\n<h2>Significant encounters in Abraham's life</h2>\n<p>With Melchizedek:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:18-Gen14:20\">GEN 14:18–14:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:1-Heb7:10\">HEB 7:1–7:10</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:1-Gen18:22\">GEN 18:1–18:22</a> <em>with three angels</em></p>\n<h2>God's covenant with Abraham</h2>\n<h3>God makes a covenant with Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:1-Gen15:21\">GEN 15:1–15:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:5-Acts7:7\">ACT 7:5–7:7</a></p>\n<h3>God gives Abram the name Abraham, as a sign of the covenant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:1-Gen17:8\">GEN 17:1–17:8</a></p>\n<h3>God gives Abraham the gift of circumcision as a sign of the covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:9-Gen17:27\">GEN 17:9–17:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:8\">ACT 7:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:11\">ROM 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>Abraham's family</h2>\n<h3>Abraham and Sarah were childless</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:30\">GEN 11:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:2-Gen15:3\">GEN 15:2–15:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:17\">GEN 17:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:11-Gen18:13\">GEN 18:11–18:13</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham's pretence that Sarah is his sister</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:10-Gen12:20\">GEN 12:10–12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:1-Gen20:18\">GEN 20:1–20:18</a></p>\n<h3>The birth of Ishmael</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:1-Gen16:4\">GEN 16:1–16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:15-Gen16:16\">GEN 16:15–16:16</a></p>\n<h3>The birth of Isaac</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:1-Gen21:7\">GEN 21:1–21:7</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham dismisses Hagar and Ishmael</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:8-Gen21:14\">GEN 21:8–21:14</a></p>\n<h3>God tests Abraham over Isaac</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:1-Gen22:19\">GEN 22:1–22:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:17-Heb11:19\">HEB 11:17–11:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:21\">JAS 2:21</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham's wife Sarah dies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:1-Gen23:2\">GEN 23:1–23:2</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham makes arrangements for a wife for Isaac</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:1-Gen24:9\">GEN 24:1–24:9</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham marries Keturah and has children by her</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:1-Gen25:2\">GEN 25:1–25:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr1:32\">1CH 1:32</a></p>\n<h3>The death of Abraham</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:7-Gen25:11\">GEN 25:7–25:11</a></p>\n<h2>The time span of Abraham's life</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:4\">GEN 12:4</a> <em>Abraham leaves Haran at the age of 75.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:3\">GEN 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:16\">GEN 16:16</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:1\">GEN 17:1</a> <em>Abraham renamed and circumcised at the age of 99</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:5\">GEN 21:5</a> <em>Isaac born when Abraham is 100</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:1\">GEN 23:1</a> <em>Sarah dies when Abraham is 137. <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:17\">Ge 17:17</a> indicates that Sarah was ten years younger than Abraham</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:7\">GEN 25:7</a> <em>Abraham dies at the age of 175.</em></p>",
